        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Looking at [diagnostic.lua](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/a0d8c2b86e788ce4273f0b8df258cd9e8e432d38/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/diagnostic.lua#L429)\r\n\r\nIt uses \"LspNotify\" auto command to register a callback for the server notifications, in this callback function it has this condition\r\n\r\n```lua\r\n        if\r\n          opts.data.method ~= ms.textDocument_didChange\r\n          and opts.data.method ~= ms.textDocument_didOpen\r\n        then\r\n          return\r\n        end\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf the document did not change it will not call the `_refresh` which refresh the ui I think\r\n\r\nWhat do you think @justinmk ",
